			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5158')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=5927&amp;FORUM_ID=6&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&amp;Topic_Title=New+way+to+%22Summon+Corpse%22"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Lets face a few facts here. Summon corpse is a royal pain in the ass since the player whose corpse you need to summon has to be both in a group with you and also in the Zone.</P><P>This is done for a couple of reasons that I can think of.</P><P>1. To prevent malicious necros (sadly they do exist) from summoning the corpse of someone they don't like into the hidden recesses of a dungeon.</P><P>2. To allow the necro summoning / conjuring the corpse to target the person whose corpse is to be summoned.</P><P>Both of these reasons are valid. However an idea just came to me that provides a way to get around these issue.</P><P>How about allowing us to summon the corpse of anyone that consents us? Specifically the last person to consent us? We could then dramatically speed up the CR on a "summons needed" CR.</P><P>The only problem that I foresee is multiple people consenting you during the time you are casting the spell. But this is nothing that a little disciple would not overcome.</P><P>Verant have often stated that they wish to reduce raid downtime. This would go a long way to acheiving just that.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>

