         I think thats a great idea. Also, I think that they should remove the ridiculous component requirements to summon corpses. I had to summon a groupmates body in TOFS a while ago. We had to port round the place to find the right coffin, then port back ect , took about an hour to actually summon his body from when he died cos I dont carry those damn jade coffins on me. By just removing the component cost perhaps this alone would make necros more desirable in groups and raids. I mean clerics dont need a component to rez someone (thank god) just lots of mana, I think it should be the same for summoning bodies. I dont think this would be overpowering in anyway, but I might just not be seeing any possible exploits.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
